ONE-MAN THEATER HELPS KILL TIME
To HELP travel-
ers while away the
time when waiting
for trains, a
man movie theater,
suitable for installa-
tion in railway ter-
minals, has been de-
signed by a New
York inventor. En-
tering the booth of
one of these devices,
a patron would seat
himself before a
miniature
and insert a coin in
a slot. An automatic
projector
then entertain him
with a current film
production until he
was ready to leave.
A number of booths
of this type would of-
fer a choice of films.
